      "writtenOn": "2026-06-02T10:49:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In the current OpenBMC codebase, the MCTP daemon implementation follows a design in which the BMC acts as the bus owner and is responsible for assigning EIDs to all downstream devices. During EID assignment, the BMC ensures that each EID is unique across the system, even when the same physical device is reachable through multiple transport interfaces such as PCIe and I2C.\n\n\nWe can not take the object path as it is - as object path belongs to the discovery object path eg /au/com/codeconstruct/mctp1/networks/1/endpoints/9\n\nSecond reason to choose the EID/IPaddress is for the readability.\nWhat do you want to keep it for the TCP discovery - hostname/ipaddress.\nI don\u0027t have any issues with either.",
      "parentUuid": "df337c9d_8760ed39",
      "revId": "eb34aeec78f6ee93993cfefd674ce6f7e211809f",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
